@startuml ap6-state
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName "Arial"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam ArrowColor #444444
skinparam ArrowFontSize 10
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.8
skinparam StateBorderThickness 1.5
skinparam StateBorderColor #555555
skinparam StateBackgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam Padding 8
skinparam RoundCorner 10

title <b>AP-6: Graceful Degradation — Sample Rate Fallback Decision</b>\n<i>Tactic: Graceful Degradation (Bass13 Performance Tactic)</i>\n<i>Linked driver: QAS-1 Real-Time Performance — guarantees Dropped Block = 0</i>

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  STATES
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

[*] --> Startup : system init

state "Startup\n«transient»" as Startup #F2F3F4 {
    state "Initialize ALSA\nat 96k sps (target)" as INIT
}

state "Running @ 96k sps\n«AP-8: 30 s ring buffer active»\n10.4 µs/sample resolution" as S96 #D5F5E3 {
    state "EXP-01: measure\nDropped Block count\nover observation window" as MEASURE
}

state "Running @ 48k sps\n«fallback — permanent once triggered»\n20.8 µs/sample resolution" as S48 #FDEDEC {
    state "Halved sample rate\nblock period: ~10 ms → ~20 ms\nDSP time budget doubled" as FALLBACK
}

state "⚠ Dropped Block\nDetected" as DROPPED #FFF3CD

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  TRANSITIONS
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

Startup      --> S96      : ALSA init success at 96k sps

S96          --> DROPPED  : Dropped Block > 0\n(Ring Buffer overflow detected)
S96          --> S96      : [Dropped Block == 0]\nkeep 96k sps ✅

DROPPED      --> S48      : reinitialize ALSA at 48k sps\n(non-reversible — permanent fallback)

S48          --> S48      : [Dropped Block == 0]\nkeep 48k sps ✅\n(normal operating state after fallback)

note right of S96
  <b>Preferred state</b>
  T1 resolution: 10.4 µs/sample
  Block period: ~10 ms
  Confirmed feasible if RPi5
  can sustain 96k sps load
  → <color:#C0392B>⚠ EXP-01 validates this</color>
end note

note right of S48
  <b>Fallback state (permanent)</b>
  T1 resolution: 20.8 µs/sample
  Block period: ~20 ms
  DSP processing budget doubled
  Dropped Block = 0 guaranteed
  Trade-off: 2× resolution loss
  → acceptable per QAS-1 target
end note

note bottom of DROPPED
  <b>Trigger condition</b>
  Ring Buffer writer (Audio Thread) detects
  that reader (DSP Thread) has not consumed
  stale blocks → overflow → Dropped Block++
  Detection is immediate per-block
end note

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  KEY
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
legend bottom
  <b>KEY</b>
  |= Symbol |= Meaning |
  | <#D5F5E3> Running @ 96k | Target operating state — preferred, higher T1 resolution |
  | <#FDEDEC> Running @ 48k | Fallback state — permanent once triggered, guarantees Dropped Block = 0 |
  | <#FFF3CD> ⚠ Dropped Block | Transient detection state — triggers irreversible fallback |
  | [Dropped Block == 0] | Guard condition — loop-back transition (system remains in current state) |
  | reinitialize ALSA at 48k | One-way transition — no return to 96k during session |

  <b>Design rationale (AP-6):</b>
  The fallback is intentionally one-way per session. Oscillating between 96k and 48k
  would cause measurement discontinuities. Stability is prioritized over peak resolution.
  ⚠ Whether 96k is achievable on RPi5 at all is confirmed by EXP-01.
endlegend

@enduml
